    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Trichotosia rubiginosa are made from its flowers, leaves and roots. A tincture is prepared by soaking the plant parts in a solvent like ethanol or glycerin to extract the bioactive compounds. An infusion is prepared by steeping the plant parts in hot water to release the active principles, while a tea is made by steeping a small amount of plant material in a large amount of hot water. A decoction is prepared by boiling the harder plant parts like roots for a longer period of time to release their active compounds. A salve is prepared by mixing the extracted bioactive compounds with a carrier oil like coconut oil or beeswax to create a topical preparation for skin issues like wounds or inflammation.",
