    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Trichotosia rubiginosa improperly include inducing nausea and causing experience nausea due to the high content of iridoid glycosides, which can have a toxic effect on the gastrointestinal system. Furthermore, improper use of Trichotosia rubiginosa may lead to experience seizures in some individuals, particularly those with a history of epilepsy or other neurological conditions. Allergic reactions can also occur, manifesting as hives, itching, or difficulty breathing, as a result of the plant's chemical composition. Additionally, vomiting is another possible side effect of using Trichotosia rubiginosa improperly, often accompanied by other symptoms such as diarrhea and abdominal pain. These side effects can be attributed to the plant's toxic compounds, which can cause harm when ingested in large quantities or without proper guidance.",
